Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced) (2 cloves for 4 servings). Place @tricolor peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in a #zip-close bag{} and crush with a #rolling pin{} or bottom of a pan.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a #medium pot{} with remaining @garlic{1%clove}, a large pinch of @salt{}, and enough water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

In #large bowl{}, soak @white bread{1}(cubed) with 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Let sit until liquid has absorbed, then break up with your hands or a #spatula{} until pasty. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, ½ tsp @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4), half the shallot, minced garlic, salt, and @pepper{}. Combine and form into two 1-inch-tall loaves. Place on one half of an oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake on top rack for ~{10%minutes}.

> If making for 4, make 4 loaves and bake until cooked through, 22-25 minutes.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @green beans{6%ounce} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Once meatloaves have baked for 10 minutes, remove from oven and place green beans on opposite side of baking sheet. Roast until beans are tender and meatloaves are fully cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Once potatoes are tender, scoop out ¼ cup cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), then drain. Return potatoes and garlic to pot. Mash with half the @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon}, adding reserved cooking water as needed, with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover pot to keep warm.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining shallot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, about ~{30%seconds}. Add ¼ cup water (½ cup for 4 servings), @beef stock concentrate{1}, and ½ tsp peppercorns (1 tsp for 4). Cook until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Turn off heat. Stir in remaining @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper (to taste).

Divide potatoes and green beans between plates. Top with meatloaves and sauce.